Tick-borne brain disease found in UK
link: A potentially fatal infection spread by ticks has been detected for the first time in the UK, according to health authorities.

title: Age just a number to rugby playing pensioners
link: The Rugby World Cup has seen rugby fever sweep across Japan as a whole new generation of Japanese rugby fans have been inspired by the incredible exploits of the country's national team, the Brave Blossoms.

title: Bulgaria gets one-time stadium ban and fine
link: Bulgaria's national soccer team has been ordered by UEFA to play its next home game behind closed doors as punishment for the "racist behavior" of its fans during a Euro 2020 against England.

title: Ex-soldier climbs 14 highest peaks
link: A former soldier from Nepal has climbed the world's 14 highest peaks in just over six months, smashing the previous record by over 7 years.

title: Huawei and ZTE could lose what little business they have in the US
link: The US Federal Communications Commission wants to place more restrictions on Huawei and ZTE by barring companies that receive government money from purchasing equipment or services from the Chinese tech firms.
